President Biden spoke at an event in Michigan, highlighting the need to invest in America's infrastructure and human capital. He emphasized the importance of rebuilding roads, bridges, and broadband, as well as investing in early childhood education and workforce development. He also discussed the need to transition to clean energy and make the United States a leader in electric vehicles. Biden stressed that these investments are necessary to compete with other countries and ensure that American workers have a fair shot at success. He addressed concerns about the cost of these investments, stating that they will be paid for by asking the wealthy to pay their fair share. He expressed confidence in the ability of the American people to rise to the challenge and build a stronger economy.